msgid "C6: Implement Digital Identity"
msgstr ""

# 0fd6294927db4ed48d56a9388a023bcb
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:3
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

# 58f108f5dc954c099f9450338b4505d5
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:5
msgid ""
"Digital Identity is the unique representation of a user (or other subject) "
"as they engage in an online transaction. Authentication is the process of "
"verifying that an individual or entity is who they claim to be. Session "
"management is a process by which a server maintains the state of the users "
"authentication so that the user may continue to use the system without re-"
"authenticating. The NIST Special Publication 800-63B: Digital Identity "
"Guidelines (Authentication and Lifecycle Management provides solid guidance "
"on implementing digital identity, authentication and session management "
"controls."
msgstr ""

# f617176ab02945b6a6f9f49c1e1f5b95
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:7
msgid "Below are some recommendations for secure implementation."
msgstr ""

# 766b3ed1a6454c53926fd1fd5efc601b
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:9
msgid "Authentication Levels"
msgstr ""

# 22dfb4ad62024545805b9d0389374979
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:11
msgid ""
"NIST 800-63b describes three levels of a authentication assurance called a "
"authentication assurance level (AAL). AAL level 1 is reserved for lower-risk"
" applications that do not contain PII or other private data. At AAL level 1 "
"only single-factor authentication is required, typically through the use of "
"a password."
msgstr ""

# ccfba008d362411dacd133d0966adecb
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:13
msgid "Level 1 : Passwords"
msgstr ""

# a8b364784afe4555be9a282ec7f43f80
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:15
msgid ""
"Passwords are really really important. We need policy, we need to store them"
" securely, we need to sometimes allow users to reset them."
msgstr ""

# 07aff991d9074bc7943fa07ba9eaea73
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:17
msgid "Password Requirements"
msgstr ""

# fc8544e9671b4c269d07ac7289d7c21c
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:19
msgid ""
"Passwords should comply with the following requirements at the very least:"
msgstr ""

# a0b56a6c18ed46b59087f7c5c4684013
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:21
msgid ""
"be at least 8 characters in length if multi-factor authentication (MFA) and "
"other controls are also used. If MFA is not possible, this should be "
"increased to at least 10 characters"
msgstr ""

# f2eec0f4d80c481ab6b73da94eb6b015
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:22
msgid ""
"all printing ASCII characters as well as the space character should be "
"acceptable in memorized secrets"
msgstr ""

# 7b0401d018ce4bb1bc555dc61648a2d4
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:23
msgid "encourage the use of long passwords and passphrases"
msgstr ""

# cd2511afae3c434b9a1b2a27803ebc88
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:24
msgid ""
"remove complexity requirements as these have been found to be of limited "
"effectiveness. Instead, the adoption of MFA or longer password lengths is "
"recommended"
msgstr ""

# ddb2e89e3afe4cd6adb7e2e9deace43e
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:25
msgid ""
"ensure that passwords used are not commonly used passwords that have been "
"already been leaked in a previous compromise.  You may choose to block the "
"top 1000 or 10000 most common passwords which meet the above length "
"requirements and are found in compromised password lists.  The following "
"link contains the most commonly found passwords: "
"https://github.com/danielmiessler/SecLists/tree/master/Passwords"
msgstr ""

# ee36812d51304a6a994c4746d6d8ab5a
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:27
msgid "Implement Secure Password Recovery Mechanism"
msgstr ""

# ce9f2a7470a64defa501694fce28ef77
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:29
msgid ""
"It is common for an application to have a mechanism for a user to gain "
"access to their account in the event they forget their password. A good "
"design workflow for a password recovery feature will use multi-factor "
"authentication elements. For example, it may ask a security question - "
"something they know, and then send a generated token to a device - something"
" they own."
msgstr ""

# 94c387e2335b4a04be8e5044813e2e01
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:31
msgid ""
"Please see the Forgot_Password_Cheat_Sheet and "
"Choosing_and_Using_Security_Questions_Cheat_Sheet for further details."
msgstr ""

# c2393a0626fe41e0899035d5f89d8276
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:33
msgid "Implement Secure Password Storage"
msgstr ""

# 30523353ba3542a39b38640774517771
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:35
msgid ""
"In order to provide strong authentication controls, an application must "
"securely store user credentials. Furthermore, cryptographic controls should "
"be in place such that if a credential (e.g., a password) is compromised, the"
" attacker does not immediately have access to this information."
msgstr ""

# 81187004646e4450b274e1cbf3e9705f
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:37
msgid "PHP Example for Password Storage"
msgstr ""

# adf3306df55f4170a0ca47bf5352b27f
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:39
msgid ""
"Below is an example for secure password hashing in PHP using  function "
"(available since 5.5.0) which defaults to using the bcrypt algorithm. The "
"example uses a work factor of 15."
msgstr ""

# d0fce0cb064c4b2fad909a42f3f828fa
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:48
msgid "Please see the OWASP Password Storage Cheat Sheet for further details."
msgstr ""

# eb4bc5d49e9a4c43b13b664939eb3398
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:50
msgid "Level 2 : Multi-Factor Authentication"
msgstr ""

# a2df659da8134298a22e75cdd865f350
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:52
msgid ""
"NIST 800-63b AAL level 2 is reserved for higher-risk applications that "
"contain \"self-asserted PII or other personal information made available "
"online.\" At AAL level 2 multi-factor authentication is required including "
"OTP or other forms of multi-factor implementation."
msgstr ""

# dc4afda3de0a49b7967608b34bcd013c
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:54
msgid ""
"Multi-factor authentication (MFA) ensures that users are who they claim to "
"be by requiring them to identify themselves with a combination of:"
msgstr ""

# 57ec82ddcd554c83b9e78f8db9112a88
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:56
msgid "Something you know – password or PIN"
msgstr ""

# cafd642791934542b1c96634ac2e4098
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:57
msgid "Something you own – token or phone"
msgstr ""

# 1cc3c32a2cb54baf893101f28ae5fc30
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:58
msgid "Something you are – biometrics, such as a fingerprint"
msgstr ""

# 31ceae7b31224a21ac240d4b9120a21e
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:60
msgid ""
"Using passwords as a sole factor provides weak security. Multi-factor "
"solutions provide a more robust solution by requiring an attacker to acquire"
" more than one element to authenticate with the service."
msgstr ""

# 2a483a01d3694924a36eaba689df3a52
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:62
msgid ""
"It is worth noting that biometrics, when employed as a single factor of "
"authentication, are not considered acceptable secrets for digital "
"authentication. They can be obtained online or by taking a picture of "
"someone with a camera phone (e.g., facial images) with or without their "
"knowledge, lifted from objects someone touches (e.g., latent fingerprints), "
"or captured with high resolution images (e.g., iris patterns). Biometrics "
"must be used only as part of multi-factor authentication with a physical "
"authenticator (something you own). For example, accessing a multi-factor "
"one-time password (OTP) device that will generate a one-time password that "
"the user manually enters for the verifier."
msgstr ""

# faebabd97a024d589e4168b32dc6c221
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:64
msgid "Level 3 : Cryptographic Based Authentication"
msgstr ""

# cd66fb44972446d28470fe4fe1a30445
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:66
msgid ""
"NIST 800-63b Authentication Assurance Level 3 (AAL3) is required when the "
"impact of compromised systems could lead to personal harm, significant "
"financial loss, harm the public interest or involve civil or criminal "
"violations. AAL3 requires authentication that is \"based on proof of "
"possession of a key through a cryptographic protocol.\" This type of "
"authentication is used to achieve the strongest level of authentication "
"assurance. This is typically done though hardware cryptographic modules."
msgstr ""

# 624561ae92604c20b6367911d162ea7a
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:68
msgid "Session Management"
msgstr ""

# 6417bac688c8409ca203878029895835
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:70
msgid ""
"Once the initial successful user authentication has taken place, an "
"application may choose to track and maintain this authentication state for a"
" limited amount of time. This will allow the user to continue using the "
"application without having to keep re-authentication with each request. "
"Tracking of this user state is called Session Management."
msgstr ""

# 5d8788d0b73e4f5e99675577538037a2
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:72
msgid "Session Generation and Expiration"
msgstr ""

# c77023750ad34574887ebe2929c643b6
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:74
msgid ""
"User state is tracked in a session. This session is typically stored on the "
"server for traditional web based session management. A session identifier is"
" then given to the user so the user can identify which server-side session "
"contains the correct user data. The client only needs to maintain this "
"session identifier, which also keeps sensitive server-side session data off "
"of the client."
msgstr ""

# 5d8dad3b615c4d23837e5094a2f59e36
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:76
msgid ""
"Here are a few controls to consider when building or implementing session "
"management solutions:"
msgstr ""

# ca784d61fb5944eea40970757e63b084
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:78
msgid "Ensure that the session id is long, unique and random."
msgstr ""

# a03314789b20427bb84d58d1bc202186
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:79
msgid ""
"The application should generate a new session or at least rotate the session"
" id during authentication and re-authentication."
msgstr ""

# 1ece335966514a3aaeda9bb368f70603
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:80
msgid ""
"The application should implement an idle timeout after a period of "
"inactivity and an absolute maximum lifetime for each session, after which "
"users must re-authenticate. The length of the timeouts should be inversely "
"proportional with the value of the data protected."
msgstr ""

# 9d2da27ac860489296dc348eef6a716e
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:82
msgid ""
"Please see the Session Management Cheat Sheet further details. ASVS Section "
"3 covers additional session management requirements."
msgstr ""

# 71c7b926a1644c1c98ddae9caf9ecbc2
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:84
msgid "Browser Cookies"
msgstr ""

# 4f4a0a6913534744ae644fb03243079d
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:86
msgid ""
"Browser cookies are a common method for web application to store session "
"identifiers for web applications implementing standard session management "
"techniques. Here are some defenses to consider when using browser cookies."
msgstr ""

# 0c3600a4ea09494ba218dacc454f2146
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:88
msgid ""
"When browser cookies are used as the mechanism for tracking the session of "
"an authenticated user,  these should be accessible to a minimum set of "
"domains and paths and should be tagged to expire at, or soon after, the "
"session's validity period."
msgstr ""

# 685e17ec8486494bab3c95a08d98e5a4
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:89
msgid ""
"The 'secure' flag should be set to ensure the transfer is done via secure "
"channel only (TLS)."
msgstr ""

# 708207a68a904b3eb4e69a531bef0a96
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:90
msgid ""
"HttpOnly flag should be set to prevent the cookie from  being accessed via "
"JavaScript."
msgstr ""

# 2a0561c626f243828f71881ccafe6c7a
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:91
msgid ""
"Adding \"samesite\" attributes to cookies prevents some modern browsers from"
" sending cookies with cross-site requests and provides protection against "
"cross-site request forgery and information leakage attacks."
msgstr ""

# 65c94adbf32c43c182f6d923f88e25ed
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:93
msgid "Tokens"
msgstr ""

# 7a01efb4180a473abdedd0cb0dd115a1
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:95
msgid ""
"Server-side sessions can be limiting for some forms of authentication. "
"\"Stateless services\" allow for client side management of session data for "
"performance purposes so they server has less of a burden to store and verify"
" user session. These \"stateless\" applications generate a short-lived "
"access token which can be used to authenticate a client request without "
"sending the user's credentials after the initial authentication."
msgstr ""

# 957e4210be7b4f94817ce7e50fb5b835
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:97
msgid "JWT (JSON Web Tokens)"
msgstr ""

# c025b48a4b0043818cd23ba6cc9fa5bb
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:99
msgid ""
"JSON Web Token (JWT) is an open standard (RFC 7519) that defines a compact "
"and self-contained way for securely transmitting information between parties"
" as a JSON object. This information can be verified and trusted because it "
"is digitally signed. A JWT token is created during authentication and is "
"verified by the server (or servers) before any processing."
msgstr ""

# 4f03a7a583534f2488154d78cf71433f
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:101
msgid ""
"However, JWT's are often not saved by the server after initial creation. "
"JWT's are typically created and then handed to a client without being saved "
"by the server in any way. The integrity of the token is maintained through "
"the use of digital signatures so a server can later verify that the JWT is "
"still valid and was not tampered with since its creation."
msgstr ""

# 0b6eb4f1bd384beb90a475f8f2750465
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:103
msgid ""
"This approach is both stateless and portable in the way that client and "
"server technologies can be different yet still interact."
msgstr ""

# ef39c154e64a47cea5bf5b3934a48f27
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:105
msgid "Caution"
msgstr ""

# ee5f74f4c4a642b78de428b8c82a1b59
#: ../../c6-implement-digital-identity.md:107
msgid ""
"Digital identity, authentication and session management are very big topics."
" We're scratching the surface of the topic of Digital Identity here. Ensure "
"that your most capable engineering talent is responsible for maintaining the"
" complexity involved with most Identity solutions."
